            <p style="text-align: center;">San Francisco International Airport (SFO) is the busiest airport in the Bay Area and the second busiest in California. It is located south of downtown San Francisco. The airport is a significant hub for major airlines such as Alaska Airlines, as well as Southwest Airlines. </p>
            <p style="text-align: center;"><b>Airport Layout and Services </b></p>
            <p style="text-align: center;">Layout- There are four terminals at SFO, designated 1, 2, 3, and International. Domestic flights operated by Alaska Airlines and American Airlines are served by Terminal 2, while domestic flights operated by Southwest Airlines and Delta Air Lines are served by Terminal 1. United Airlines uses Terminal 3 for both domestic and international flights. The international terminal handles all international and a few domestic flights operated by carriers like Air Canada, British Airways, and Emirates. SFO is known for having one of the greenest airports in the entire world. Numerous programs have been put in place by the airport to lessen its carbon footprint, including the use of alternative fuel vehicles, energy-efficient lighting, and heating systems, and the use of renewable energy. SFO was the first airport in the world to receive LEED Gold certification for its environmentally conscious Terminal 2. Services- Travelers can take advantage of a range of amenities and services at SFO. These consist of a variety of eateries, cafes, and bars, in addition to duty-free stores, newsstands, and gift shops. The SFO Museum, which displays changing exhibits on a variety of subjects, including art, science, and history, is another facility within the airport. There are also free Wi-Fi hotspots available throughout the airport, electronic device charging stations, and a pet relief area. Transportation- The area around SFO is highly linked. There is a BART station near the airport that makes it simple to go to downtown San Francisco and other Bay Area destinations. Additionally, there are many ground transportation choices available at the airport, including taxis, ride-hailing services, and rental cars. </p>
            <p style="text-align: center;">SFO is an increasingly popular destination for tourists from all around the world. With more than 57 million passengers passing through each year, the airport is among the busiest in the country. The airport is renowned for its smooth operations, excellent customer service, and state-of-the-art amenities. </p>
            <p style="text-align: center;">All things considered, San Francisco International Airport is a top-notch facility that acts as a vital entry point to the San Francisco Bay Area and beyond. SFO is a preferred choice for visitors worldwide with its cutting-edge amenities, eco-friendly initiatives, and excellent transport connections. </p>
